# Vite build-time env. Copy to .env.local for local override.
#
# Where the React app should send `/api/*` calls.
# - Dev: leave empty so the Vite proxy (vite.config.ts) forwards /api → http://127.0.0.1:8000
# - Prod: MUST be set to the public API origin including the /api prefix,
#   e.g. https://your-api-service.onrender.com/api
#
# If this is unset for a production build, the deployed bundle will hardcode
# http://localhost:8000/api, which won't work from a user's browser AND will
# make the "Continue with Google" button 404 on the static-site origin.
# VITE_API_BASE=https://your-api-service.onrender.com/api
